"The Letter M Song" (See below for lyrics)

The soulful lead soloist and tight harmonies of the back-up singers add a marvelous groove to disco and "The Letter M Song" in particular. While vinyl records are no longer commonly in use, your child can still have a great time playing DJ. Make a mix CD or MP3 playlist with your child so that you have something groovy like "The Letter M Song" to listen and dance to together. 

About Us: 
ABCmouse.com is an award-winning website that uses a variety of activities, including these songs, to help children build a strong foundation for future academic success. ABCmouse.com Early Learning Academy provides a full online curriculum in preschool, pre-k, and kindergarten, with more than 5,000 interactive learning activities that teach the subjects of reading, math, science, social studies, art, and music.

Parents, learn more about ABCmouse.com at http://ABCmouse.com/LearnMore.

Song Lyrics: 
You have to press your lips together when you say the letter m. 
Words like mittens, moon and marshmallow 
are just a few of them. 
Let's make a little music as you sing along with me. 
Listen for the m words in this little melody. 

Max the monkey mashed mangos and melons 
and topped that mix off with a cherry. 
Whenever he'd munch on this mishmash for lunch, 
each mouthful made Max feel so merry. 

So let's hear it for m. You know it so well. 
When you sing about m words, it's easy to tell. 
So open your mouths, and let's give a yell 
for the marvelous letter that comes after l: letter m! 

Mike the marine wrote a message to Mindy 
and mailed that message on a Monday. 
The message he mailed said, "If you marry me, 
we'll be Mr. and Mrs. this coming Sunday!" 

So let's hear it for m. You know it so well. 
When you sing about m words, it's easy to tell. 
So open your mouths, and let's give a yell 
for the marvelous letter that comes after l: letter m!

M is for mother and marble and moo, 
muffins and mushrooms and mulligan stew.  
Munchkins are small. Mammoths are tall. 
A mackerel's a fish, and a minnow is too. Whoo-hoo! 

So let's hear it for m. You know it so well. 
When you sing about m words, it's easy to tell. 
So open your mouths, and let's give a yell 
for the marvelous letter that comes after l: 
letter m, letter m, letter m!

We took a day charter trip with Sooke Coastal Fishing Charters to target Halibut and they didn't disappoint.

We were about a 15 minute boat ride from the docks in Sooke to the fishing grounds where we caught the two Halibut. One was about 15 lbs and the other about 25 lbs,

The sun was out full force and so was the wind and waves. but that didn't stop us from having a blast jigging for halibut.

We each walked away with enough Halibut to last us quite some time. Thank you Sooke Coastal Fishing Charters for a great day of Halibut Fishing.

Snubber or Pulsation Dampener fittings protects pressure  gauges and instruments from system pressure surges and shock. Pressure damping (snubbing) is accomplished through the use of a porous sintered SS 316 element. When snubber is installed up stream from a pressure instruments , the response rate of the instrument is reduced and generally varies with the initial pressure drop across the porous metal element, and allows the instrument to smoothly come to line ressure.

Pulsation dampeners are designed to improve readability and prevent wear on delicate gauge mechanisms where pressure spikes and pulsations may be present. These dampeners are offered in a choice of connections and body materials.
title: Snubber or Pulsation Dampener - protects pressure gauges and instruments

Homemade Nutella spread aka Chocolate Hazelnut Spread

Makes 650 ml

Ingredients:
(220 grams) 2 cups of whole hazelnut, skin removed
(160 grams) 1 ¼ cup of icing sugar
(45 grams) 1/3 cup of unsweetened cocoa powder
(185 ml) 3/4 cup of milk
2 tsp. of vanilla extract
1 tsp. vegetable oil 
1/8 tsp. of salt

Directions:

1. Preheat oven to 200C.

2. Roast hazelnut for about 10 minutes.

3. Transfer them into a food processor, blitz for about 5 minutes until it turns into a liquid. Scrape down once in a while.
 
4. Add in the rest of the ingredients. Process until smooth and combined. It may looks runny but once it cools it will get thicker.

5. Transfer them into an airtight container. I put mine into mason jars. 

6. Keep them in the fridge so that they can last for up to 4 months.

TOP 10 Bowlers Banned For Illegal Bowling Action

1-Saeed Ajmal

Saeed Ajmal, who has been Pakistan's lead spinner in recent years, was banned in September 2014.
Ajmal was reported during the first Test against Sri Lanka in 2014.
He has been banned from bowling in international cricket by the ICC after his action was found illegal for all deliveries.

2-Shoaib Akhtar

Pakistani fast bowler Shoaib Akhtar was banned by ICC in December 1999 but overturned almost immediately.
In an interview he admitted that the decision of the ICC to ban him was worse than the injury problems.
ICC banned Shoaib Akhtar for a suspected bowling action on Eve of New Year in the year 2000.

3-Sachithra Senanayake

Sri Lankan cricketer Sachithra Senanayake was banned from bowling in international cricket in July 2014.
Senanayake was reported for a suspect action during Sri Lanka's fourth ODI against England on May 31, 2014.
Senanayake has been banned from bowling in international cricket, after his action was found to be illegal.

4-Marlon Samuels

West Indian Marlon Samuels has been suspended from bowling for suspect bowling actions by the ICC.
Samuels was first reported in 2008 after which he didn't bowl for the next three years.
Once again he was banned in December 2013 from bowling quicker deliveries in international cricket.

5- Abdur Razzak

Bangladeshi cricketer Abdur Razzak was banned from bowling in December 2008  for suspect bowling action.
Razzak’s bowling action was reported by umpires after New Zealand's tour of Bangladesh in October 2008.
In March 2009, the ICC lifted Razzak's suspension and allowed him after he changed his bowling action.

6-Johan Botha

South African cricketer Johan Botha was prohibited from bowling in February 2006 by ICC for suspect actions. 
In November 2006, he was cleared to resume bowling at international level after he rectified his action. 
He was again reported in April 2009, and his doosra was banned.

7- Shane Shillingford

West Indian cricketer Shane Shillingford was banned from bowling on two occasions for suspectwd action.
Shillingford was banned from bowling in 2010 but returned to bowl in 2011 after undergoing remedial work.
Shillingford was reported in November 2013 again and banned in December 2013 by the ICC. 

8-James Kirtley

Robert James Kirtley is a former English Test cricketer, who played 11 ODIs and 4 Tests.
He was suspended from bowling by England & Wales Cricket Board (ECB) in 2005 for his bowling action.
In 2001-02 he was also reported by the match referee on his one-day debut match in Zimbabwe.

9-Shabbir Ahmed

Pakistani pace bowler Shabbir Ahmed was banned by ICC for an illegal bowling action in December 2005 for 1 year.
In 2005 after playing the first Test against England he was reported to the ICC for an illegal bowling action. 
His action was reported on multiple occasions, first in 1999 again in January 2004 and twice in 2005.

10-Kane Williamson

Kane Stuart Williamson is a New Zealand Test cricketer, who was banned by ICC in July 2014.
The off-spinner was reported to the ICC after second Test against West Indies in June 2014.
He has been banned from bowling in international and domestic cricket because of an illegal action.

El rebollo (Quercus pyrenaica), también llamado roble melojo, carballo negro, etc, es un árbol de hoja caduca, marcescente y de talla más pequeña que la de sus hermanos el Quercus robur y petraea. Tiene el tronco recto, irregular y corteza estriada, grisácea.

Brota abundantemente de raíz, dando bosques y bosquetes de gran densidad.

Sus hojas son lobuladas, con los entrantes muy marcados llegando casi hasta el nervio. Color verde por el haz y con pelos en el envés. El peciolo es corto.

El fruto es la bellota, cuya cúpula llega hasta 1/3 del fruto y tiene el pedúnculo muy corto. Maduran en otoño y, al  igual que la encina y el quejigo, son fáciles de hacer germinar. Para sembralas basta con enterrarlas entre 2 y 4 cm en la tierra o sustrato, en posición tumbada. Cuanto antes se siembren desde la recogida de la semilla mejor porque van perdiendo viabilidad y su conservación por estratificación es delicada. Para saber si son viables basta echarlas en agua y descartar las que floten. Se pueden sembrar en su sitio definitivo (inconveniente: se la pueden comer los ratones, jabalíes, etc) o en contendor (alveolo forestal preferentemente) y luego transplantar.

El rebollo es muy resistente al frío y prefiere sustratos ácidos. Sustituye a la encina en altura y necesita más humedad.

Se usa mucho para leña y también se ha utilizado para hacer carbón.

Más sobre el rebollo o melojo (Quercus pyrenaica) en: http://riomoros.blogspot.com/2011/03/el-rebollo-quercus-pyrenaica.html
title: EL REBOLLO: Quercus pyrenaica (http://riomoros.blogspot.com.es/)

Nairobi ODM Chairman George Aladwa was on Saturday arrested and is being held at the Central Police Station. He is accused of calling for the swearing in of Former Prime Minister Raila Odinga on the 7th of July. Aladwa was arrested at midday for his alleged remarks calling for the swearing in of CORD leader Raila Odinga as president. This comes as the government is taking stringent measures on remarks that constitute hatespeech. The ODM team has however distanced itself from Aladwa's remarks with acting party leader Anyang Nyong' saying that it is not the official position of the ODM party. Aladwa on the other hand insists that he is the party leader since delegates elected him. It has not yet been confirmed what charges Aladwa will be facing.

description:
Pour cette seconde session nous avons gravi un échelon avec Da Silva. Nous nous étions rencontré pour la première fois au sous sol d'un bar parisien. cette fois ci c'est au rez de chaussé d'un hôtel du même arrondissement, le IXe. La session a été calée en fonction de la fin d'une interview de Françoise Hardy pour la nouvelle émission de France 2, Alcaline. 

Dans le salon rouge de l'Hôtel Alba, l'hôtel des sessions PIAS, Manu Da Silva et ses musiciens ont installé une petite sono, pendant que nous nous installons cela discute sur la manière de jouer les deux morceaux prévus. Tout le monde va jouer moins fort que la session précédente, Manu est obligé de caler sa voix différemment, de s'adapter et le premier morceau joué "le coureur de fond" dégage tout de suite quelque chose de beau et touchant. Cette façon de jouer très différente de l'album nous montre encore une fois que même si ici nous sommes loin de l'acoustique ce qui nous touche et nous plait dans les sessions c'est quand les artistes nous proposent quelque chose de différent, de nouveau. 

Un vrai et beau cadeau. 

Merci à l'Hôtel Alba.

Images : Renaud de Foville (www.unjourpeutetre.net)

description:
Scholar: ´Allâmah Sâlih bin Fawzân al-Fawzân
Source: al-nasiha.net/voices.php?action=show&id=­5
Reference: Darulhadith.com
Audio and translation courtesy of http://www.aFatwa.com

Question: We are a group of security men who have a question for you. We have received a task to expose those who plan to jolt the security and revolt against the ruler. We have heard of a Fatwâ that says that it is not allowed to follow and fight against these people because they fight for the sake of Allâh and (they) want to drive out the disbelievers who fight against the Muslims in other countries, such as Iraq. Which opinion is the correct one in this matter?

Shaykh al-Fawzân: May Allâh aid you! You are in Jihâd when performing this deed [I.e. exposing those in question]. Your intention is to hit back at the people of falsehood and preserve the security, life, honour, and property. You are in Jihâd. May Allâh aid you and reward you with the reward of the Mujâhidûn. You are likewise obeying the ruler of the Muslims. The deed you are performing is very noble. Therefore, do not doubt.

As for those who are saying that this is Jihâd; whom are they? Have any of the recognized scholars said that this is Jihâd? Never! This is a lie. The fact of the matter is that this deed involves declaring Muslim blood lawful to spill and making rebellion against the ruler. All of this is disobedience and great sins and refuge is sought with Allâh. Thus, this does not belong to Jihâd. This is for the sake of Shaytân (Satan) and not for the sake of Allâh. It harms the Muslims.

Regarding expelling disbelievers, then this is not up to you (those in question). The one who drives out the disbelievers is the ruler. He is the one who grants them security, lets them enter the country due to those advantages the Muslims are in need of. He expels them when their time has expired. The prophet (sallâ Allâhu 'alayhi wa sallam) said:

"Expel the polytheists from the Arabian peninsula."

(al-Bukhârî 2888 and Muslim 1637)

This address is directed towards the rulers. 'Umar (radhiya Allâhu 'anh) was thusly the first one to expel them. The other citizens did not do it. The one who expels the disbelievers and brings them in is the ruler. They did not come as soldiers. They came in order to carry out work in diplomacy or business. The Muslims brought them for their own benefit. They received security and pact when they entered. The prophet (sallâ Allâhu 'alayhi wa sallam) said:

"The one who kills a disbeliever who has received a pact (Mu'âhad) will not be able to smell the fragrance of Paradise, and its fragrance extends (to the distance of) seventy years."

(al-Bukhârî 3166)

This is a harsh threat.

The one who says that it is Jihâd is either knowledgeable in deviance, if he possesses knowledge, or he is also really ignorant without knowing what Jihâd for Allâh's sake is.
title: War Against The Terrorists is From Jihâd! | Shaykh al-Fawzân

description:
Lightning Strikes New President's Plane 
Published: May 15, 2012, 2:11 PM EDT weather.com
New French President Francois Hollande looks out of his car as he rides up the Champ-Elysses after the presidential handover ceremony Tuesday.
Tuesday wasn't a good day weather-wise for France's new president, Francois Hollande.
First, his inauguration was marred by dreary skies and then his journey to Berlin for key talks with German Chancellor Angela Merkel was delayed after his plane was hit by lightning, the BBC reported.
The plane was forced to turn back to Paris. Hollande took a second plane and was expected to arrive in Berlin later today.
Earlier Tuesday, Hollande was sworn into a five-year term at the Elysee Palace in Paris, becoming France's first Socialist president in 17 years.
http://www.weather.com/news/french-president-20120515

description:
Output: blue gear with a male cone. The red arrow represents load (to be raised or descended) applied to the gear.
The yellow ratchet wheel with a female cone rotates idly. It is connected to the violet crank by the white ring and two red springs. The crank makes a helical joint with the orange shaft.
The video shows three stages for the load: 
1. Moving up: The crank is turned clockwise (the blue arrow). Due to the helical joint the crank presses the ratchet wheel towards the blue gear to close the cone clutch, hence the gear rotates to move up the load. The crank, the ratchet wheel, the gear and the orange shaft rotate together.
2. Stop (no force applied to the crank): The load tends to turn the blue disk anticlockwise but the springs maintain the press from the crank, hence the closing state of the clutch is continued. The pawl brakes the load from descending.
3. Moving down:  The crank is pushed (not turned) anticlockwise (the pink arrow). Due to the helical joint the crank moves a little to the right to disclose the cone clutch, hence the gear can rotates to move down the load. If the crank is released, the springs pull the crank to close the clutch to brake the load.
Thus the crank does not rotate during descending the load to avoid accidents.
The key factor is the right hand thread of the orange shaft in this case.
title: Safety crank for windlass

description:
A powerful 7.2-magnitude earthquake struck eastern Turkey Sunday, collapsing about 45 buildings according to the deputy prime minister.

Only one death was immediately confirmed, but scientists estimated that up to 1,000 people could have been killed.

The worst damage was caused to the town of Ercis, in the mountainous eastern province of Van, close to the Iranian border. The city of Van also suffered substantial damage.

"Around 10 buildings have collapsed in the city of Van and around 25 or 30 have collapsed in Ercis, including a dormitory," Deputy Prime Minister Besir Atalay said.

Atalay said authorities had no information yet on remote villages, adding that the governor was now touring the region by helicopter to assess damage. The quake's epicenter was in the village of Tabanli.

Authorities did not provide a casualty figure but the Kandilli observatory, Turkey's main seismography center, said the quake was capable of killing many more people.

"We are estimating a death toll between 500 and 1,000," Mustafa Erdik, head of the Kandilli observatory, told a televised news conference. His estimate was based on the structure of the housing in the area and the strength of the quake.
title: Eastern Turkey Earthquake Update

Music from Australia and New Zealand in the year 1969:

The Valentines [ performing on Turning On ] the song 'Build Me Up Buttercup' (The Foundations cover) in 1969.

Note: It must be pointed out to non-Australian viewers that the Valentines were one of the most popular teen-pop bands in Australia during the late '60's and would be remembered to this day, with or without the Bon Scott connection.

Also, many of the band's early songs were written by Harry Vanda and George Young of Easybeats fame... one of them, George, being the brother of Angus and Malcolm Young.

The Valentines were teen-bop group that launched the careers of two crucial figures in Australian rock: Bon Scott (later of AC/DC - seen as the backing singer who is not playing an instrument) and Vince Lovegrove (main guy in front singing - who would later introduce Bon Scott to AC/DC and a few years later become manager of Divinyls. Vince has also made a name for himself as a television compeer, producer and reporter... cheers!).

description:
For engines equipped with common rail injection technology, the injection pressure is generated independently of the load and engine speed. To enable this, the injection pressure build-up is separated from the injection process.
A high-pressure pump generates the necessary fuel pressure, which is stored in a high-pressure accumulator (the rail) from where it is available to all injectors at all times. These injectors have extremely fast solenoid valves that are actuated electronically. This results in a great amount of flexibility in designing the injection process. At MAN, up to 3 partial injections are currently used per work cycle. As a result, a freely selectable common rail system pressure can be produced for all cylinders across the entire operating speed range of the engine.
An optimised injection process with ideal atomisation under high injection pressure can thus be achieved even at low engine speeds. For design reasons, this freely selectable build-up of system pressure is not possible for cam-controlled systems such as pump nozzle (PN) and unit pump system (UPS). The pressure level for these systems fluctuates depending on the load and engine speed. The largely free configuration of the injection parameters, as enabled by the common rail system, is not possible in this case.
title: Function of the common rail fuel injection system

description:
Steps:

1 - Heat up the water in the stove.
Make sure the water does NOT boil. It just has to get to the exact point before it boils. If it does boil, let it cool for a while before continuing.
If you mix boiling water with coffee you free the acids in the coffee. On a long term and high amounts these acids are toxic for human beings.

2 - While the water is getting warmer pour 10 grams of coffee per cup of water into a pot and distribute it uniformly.
If you like it strong, pour more coffee.

3 - Pour the hot water over the coffee.

4 - Wait 30 seconds and push down to the bottom the little crust that grows in the surface.

5 - Wait 3 minutes.

6 - Remove the little frothiness that is at the top of the coffee. This is the part of the coffee that affects people who have gastritis.

7 - Let it cool at least two more minutes and serve.

Enjoy!


Recommendation: try it without sugar. :D
title: How to make boiled coffe?

New Book on Shamanism in Pre-Christian Europe -"The Thunder Wizard Path" Now available in paperback or instant download. at lulu.com or http://www.ThunderWizard.com
Have you tried Eastern spiritual practices, but you just don't relate to them? Have you secretly yearned for an authentic Western, Earth-based, shamanic, spiritual practice but you have been dissapointed with some of the New Age religions? The Thunder Wizard Path is a modern shamanic practice derived from spiritual principles contained in the Mythological lore of the pre-Christian Teutonic people of northern Europe. Embedded within the Norse myths are coded instructions for absorbing universal life force energy (qigong), shamanism and spiritual transformation. Author Michael William Denney has spent 20 years researching and decoding spiritual secrets contained within the mythologies of India and China. In The Thunder Wizard Path, Mr. Denney takes his understanding of these sacred teachings and applies it to the myths of his ancestors - the Teutons. What he reveals is a mystery religion of such power and beauty as to rival the Vedic scriptures, the Tantric Sutras and the Tao Te Ching. Shamanism and Wizardry were practiced in northern Europe continuously for 50,000 years. Now these practices are being revealed once again for our generation.

description: Fishing for yellow-eyed mullet in Christchurch, N.Z. This species is found all around New Zealand. Although a sea fish it enters estuaries and coast rivers to feed. They can be caught with fine mesh set nets and casting nets. Mullet respond well to berley and will readily take small baited hooks and flies. Big ones can reach 40cm but most are much smaller. They make excellent surfcasting bait. Most of all they are great fun to catch from a riverbank or jetty and are an ideal target when taking kids fishing. The best bait is live ghost shrimp yabbies (which are sucked out of the sand on a beach at low tide). In this video Allan Burgess is catching yellow-eyed mullet in the lower Waimakariri and Kaiapoi Rivers.
title: Yellow-eyed Mullet Fishing

description:
Australia is always associated with kangaroos. There are tens of thousands of them, and several species. 
The eastern grey kangaroo, also known as the great grey kangaroo, is a marsupial found in southern and eastern Australia and in the Blue Mountains.
It is a big fellow, but it is not the largest kangaroo in Australia; the red kangaroo of the semi-arid inland is larger.
The colours between the different animals vary from silver grey to dark grey. The females go around in groups, while the males travel the area on their own. The females will only mate with a dominant male and he will chase away all other enthusiasts.
Kangaroo births seem a non stop business. When the young - or joey - is only four months old the female mates again. The remarkable thing is that the foetus will only develop when the pouch is empty, so when the young can more or less stand on his own two feet.
Females mate for the first time when they are 18 months old. The gestation period lasts 33 to 38 days. After birth the young will use its mothers pouch as a safe hiding place for about 11 months.
Broadcast format available at: http://www.stockshot.nl/
title: eastern grey kangaroo - macropus giganteus

To attach rigid foam insulation or lath for stucco or stone veneer  walls Rodenhouse Inc. has developed quick and efficient methods of attachment.  Our fasteners and tools will save time and money on installation over wood, steel, or masonry substrates.  
To attach rigid foam insulation, the Thermal-Grip ci washers have pre-spotting prongs which allow for quick on-the-wall screw assembly.  Our Grip-Deck ceramic coated screws have superior corrosion resistance  and are available in self-drilling for steel or hi-lo thread for wood substrates. 
The Grip-Lock auto-feed system with Bullseye nose adaptor quickly auto-centers over the head of the Thermal-Grip ci prong washer allowing for rapid attachment of insulation while preventing overdrive of the washer through the foam insulation. 
When using bulk screws and washers, utilize the EZ-Driver chuck adaptor which allows for depth control adjustment and eliminates wobbling of screws when drilling into heavy gauge steel studs. 
These same great tools can be utilized when attaching either metal or fiberglass lath. The Bullseye nose adaptor is available with magnetic end for placement of Grip Plate washer on the screwgun allowing for one hand operation and rapid attachment of lath, even into steel studs. Grip Plate washers are available flat or with tabs and are galvanized for corrosion protection.

The 2014 Bentley Flying Spur weighs 5,580 lbs and carries the same twin-turbo 6.0-litre W12 used in the Continental GT, for an output of 600 horsepower and 533 pound-feet of torque. The Bentley Flying Spur has a zero-to-sixty-mph time of 4.5 seconds and a top speed of 200 mph. The Bentley Flying Spur steering column-mounted paddle shifters enable direct access to the six-speed gearbox when the ZF transmission is in "S" or sports mode. EPA Bentley Flying Spur MPG fuel economy estimates are 11 mpg city/19 mpg highway. A 2014 Bentley Continental Flying Spur comes with a 3 year/unlimited mileage warranty. The 2014 Bentley Flying Spur Price Speed version carries a $209,600 base price. Bentley Flying Spur Options include a remote-controlled rear-seat entertainment system embedded in the front row headrests. Lambswool rugs accompany the Bentley Flying Spur Premium specification.
On 12 February 2013, Bentley Motors announced a redesigned Flying Spur for model-year 2014.[1] The 2014 Bentley Flying Spur was first unveiled to the public at the 2013 Geneva Motor Show.[2] The "Continental" prefix has been omitted from Bentley's promotional material for this model. Bentley Flying Spur carries the same twin-turbo 6.0-litre W12 used in the Continental GT, for an output of 616 horsepower, 590 pound-feet of torque and zero-to-sixty-mph time of 4.3 seconds. The Bentley Flying Spur sedan weighs 5,451 pounds and has a new eight-speed automatic transmission for the 2014 Bentley Flying Spur model-year. Bentley Flying Spur's all-wheel-drive system is rear-biased with a ratio of 60:40.

The 2014 Bentley Flying Spur MPG is expected to get better fuel economy by U.S. EPA estimates, with (uncertified) projections of 12 miles per gallon (mpg) in the city and 20 mpg on the highway.
The Bentley Continental Flying Spur is a four-door variant of the Bentley Continental GT coupé. The Bentley Flying Spur was introduced in 2005. This car shares its platform with the Volkswagen Phaeton, and its powertrain components are related to those on the Audi A8 and S8. It was designed by the same team as produced the Continental GT and Continental GTC.
Bentley Flying Spur Changes include increasing engine performance (from Continental GT Speed), ZF eight-speed transmission, redesigned body with lower, wider appearance with sharp lines and gently curvaceous surfaces; new wing vent at front fenders, new body structure includes reinforcement to the B-posts, sills and front crossmembers together with deformable components in the floorpan for optimal load transfer; a deployable aluminium bonnet that includes both new reinforcement panels and deformation elements, 600 new interior parts, lightweight acoustic underfloor panels, side glazing and both front and rear screens made in acoustic glass, heating and ventilation system with a new Thermostatic Expansion Valve (with optional Climate Boost function), new 19" tyre with 12% relative increase in sidewall height, Bentley Flying Spur suspension spring rates are softened front and rear by 10% and 13% respectively, anti-roll bars softened by 13 per cent and 15 per cent to improve single wheel impact absorption, suspension lever bushes all-round softened by at least 25 per cent for reduced road surface-induced noise and vibration, revised damper electronic control (CDC), new 19-inch Classic wheel in bright-painted or with a diamond turned finish (optional 20-inch five-spoke, 21-inch six-spoke and 21-inch ten-spoke wheels).

Bentley Flying Spur W12 Mulliner includes five additional hides, expanding the number of available shades to 17, five further wood veneers choices, 21-inch five-spoke two-piece alloy wheels, Mulliner name at treadplates and the chrome details on the wing vent, diamond-quilted seats and door panels with perforated hides, drilled alloy sports pedals and a knurled sports gear lever.

The "Continental" prefix has been omitted from Bentley's promotional material for this facelift model. According to Bentley's designers, this was a conscious attempt to distance the Flying Spur - a 4-door limousine - from the 2-door Continental GT range[28] (historically, the Continental name was generally used by Bentley to refer to 2-door models). 

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bentley_Continental_Flying_Spur_%282005%29#Flying_Spur

description:
Arthur Rimbaud  Born 20/10/1854 à Charleville "France" Die: 10/11/1891 à Marseille France .
En 1870 Arthur. Rimbaud écrit Ma Bohème  il a 16 ans. Ce poème évoque une ou plusieurs de ses fugues. 
Rimbaud fuit un milieu étouffant et conformiste. Il s'agit d'un sonnet de forme traditionnelle, plein de fantaisie, de jeunesse illustrant les errances adolescentes de Rimbaud. 
Written at the age of 16, my Boheme evokes one or more of its runaway. Rimbaud fled an environment stifling and conformist.
This is a traditional form of light sonnet, full of whims of youth that illustrate the vagaries of teenage Rimbaud.

My Vagabondage

I would take to the road, with my fists in my holey pockets
and a coat that was getting more virtual than real.
I would walk beneath the sky, oh Muse, as your devotee.
Wow, what splendid loves I dreamt of then!

There was a big hole in my only trousers,
and as I walked, a dreamy Tom Thumb, I would count out
lines of verse. My inn was the Sign of the Great Bear.
In the sky my stars made a gentle rustling.

And I'd listen to them, while sitting at the roadside
on those good September nights when I could feel drops
of dew on my forehead, like invigorating wine.

There, making poems amid fantastical shadows,
I would stretch and pluck like lyre-strings the laces
of my wounded shoes, with one foot up near my heart.

Translation from french to English  by Peter low

description:
Take a tour of Malacca A Famosa Ruins in Malacca, Malaysia  -- part of the World's Greatest Attractions travel video series by GeoBeats.
 
The ruins of the A Famosa fortress are an impressive piece of history, even though only the gatehouse remains.

This fort, built by the Portuguese in 1511, is located in Malacca, Malaysia, once a part of the Portuguese Empire.

Construction on the fort began almost immediately after the Portuguese captured Malacca, to prepare for potential resistance.

A Famosa later was transferred to Dutch control and then to British, who wanted to destroy it for strategic military reasons.

When pickaxes and crowbars proved to be insufficient to damage the walls, explosives were used in the demolition.

Near the end of the demolition, Sir Stamford Raffles was able to preserve the last bit of A Famosa, the gatehouse.
title: Malacca A Famosa Ruins, Malacca (Malaysia) - Travel Guide

Included on this dvd are six effects you can do with ANY deck of cards, PLUS two bonus routines and a incredibly simple yet deceptive move to switch a card that has not been released any where, ever! It is finally shared here in a special section with over 35 - minutes of in depth detail, recorded in full HD. This is real world magic, that you will perform! Ranging from renditions on classics to incredible SELF-WORKING routines, this dvd is a must for anyone who loves card magic. 

New Found Blood: A multi-phase sandwich and coincidence routine with a killer ending and even includes 3 variations! 

Two Ton Triumph: An in the hands triumph with a super clean get ready, to eliminate any "fishy moves". Perfect for the walk around performer or anyone looking for an anytime, anywhere version of Michael's Modern Triumph. 

No Stopping Me: A self working routine done under impossible conditions. You can have a card looked at in the deck, have the spectator deal through and stop them at their card! The perfect stop trick, with a great psychological through off.

description:
Ogden Kraut was able to find out one important detail left out of the official version as stated below. His son, Kevin Kraut shares what else Ogden learned in the video.

This is recounted by Le Roi Clarence Snow, son of Lorenzo Snow.

For some time President Woodruff's health had been failing. Nearly every evening President Lorenzo Snow visited him at his home on South 5th East Street. This particular evening the doctors said President Woodruff was failing rapidly and they feared he would not live much longer. Lorenzo Snow was then President of the Council of Twelve and was greatly worried over the possibility of succeeding President Woodruff, especially because of the terrible financial condition of the Church. Referring to this, President Heber J. Grant had said: "The Church was in a financial slough of despond, so to speak, almost financially bankrupt—its credit was hardly good for a thousand dollars without security."

My father went to his room in the Salt Lake Temple, where he was residing at the time. He dressed in his robes of the Priesthood, went into the Holy of Holies, and knelt at the sacred altar. He plead with the Lord to spare President Woodruff's life, that he might outlive him and that the great responsibility of Church leadership would never fall upon his shoulders. Yet he promised the Lord that he would devotedly perform any duty required at his hands. At this time he was in his eighty-sixth year.

Soon after this President Woodruff was taken to California, where he died Friday morning at 6:40 a.m., September 2, 1898. President George Q. Cannon at once wired the sad information to the President's office in Salt Lake City. Word was forwarded to President Snow who was in Brigham City. The telegram was delivered to him on the street in Brigham. He read it to President Rudger Clawson, then president of the Box Elder Stake, who was with him, went to the telegraph office and replied that he would leave on the train about 5:30 p.m., he then went to his private room in the Salt Lake Temple, put on his holy temple robes, repaired again to the same sacred altar, offered up the signs of the Priesthood; and poured out his heart to the Lord. He prayed, "Thy will be done. I have not sought this responsibility but if it be Thy will, I now present myself before Thee for Thy guidance and instruction. I ask that Thou show me what Thou wouldst have me do."

After finishing his prayer he expected a reply, some special manifestation from the Lord. So he waited—and waited—and waited. There was no reply, no voice, no visitation, no manifestation. He left the altar and the room in great disappointment. He passed through the Celestial room and into the large corridor leading to his own room where a most glorious manifestation was given President Snow. One of the most beautiful accounts of this experience is told by his granddaughter, Allie Young Pond.

"One evening when I was visiting Grandpa Snow in his room in the Salt Lake Temple, I remained until the doorkeepers had gone and the nightwatchman had not yet come in, so grandpa said he would take me to the main, front entrance and let me out that way. He got his bunch of keys from his dresser.

"After we left his room and while we were still in the large corridor, leading into the celestial room, I was walking several steps ahead of grandpa when he stopped me, saying: 'Wait a moment, Allie. I want to tell you something. It was right here that the Lord Jesus Christ appeared to me at the time of the death of President Woodruff. He instructed me to go right ahead and reorganize the First Presidency of the Church at once and not wait as had been done after the death of the previous presidents, and that I was to succeed President Woodruff.'

"Then Grandpa came to a step nearer and held out his left hand and said: 'He stood right here, about three feet above the floor. It looked as though he stood on a plate of solid gold.' 
"Grandpa told me what a glorious personage the Savior is and described His hands, feet, countenance and beautiful White Robes, all of which were of such a glory of whiteness and brightness that he could hardly gaze upon Him.

"Then Grandpa came another step nearer me and put his right hand on my head and said: 'Now, granddaughter, I want you to remember that this is the testimony of your grandfather, that he told you with his own lips that he actually saw the Savior here in the Temple and talked with Him face to face.' description:
The Quadski reaches speeds of 45 mph (72 km/h) on both water and land and transitions between them in seconds. At the press of a button the Quadski's wheels deploy when approaching land and retract after entering the water.

Previously, no commercially available amphibian has been able to exceed 10 mph (16 km/h) on water. The difference is the breakthrough GIBBS patented technology provides unique on-water performance. Unmatched freedom on water AND land, and rapid in transition - Quadski sets a new standard in flexibility, freedom and fun for personal watercraft.

Quadski is powered by BMW Motorrad's K1300 engine. On water the BMW engine is coupled with GIBBS patented water jet propulsion system. The Quadski is capable of attaining speeds of 45 mph (72 km/h) on both water and land. Excellent performance and comfortable ride are the result of a light weight composite hull, wide track and low centre of gravity, which gives Quadski robust stability on water and land.

Incorporating GIBBS HSA technology, the Quadski hull provides a stable planing surface and lateral grip for responsive handling on water. The hull is designed to be hydrodynamic in marine mode. The Quadski's hull is strong, durable, light-weight and is manufactured from a single-piece mould using current composite technology.

GIBBS jet units are lighter and more compact than traditional marine industry water jets and provide high levels of thrust and manoeuverability on water. Water jet propulsion also provides responsive manoeuverability at low speeds and reverse while providing power to cruise at planing speeds. GIBBS water jet technology can propel the Quadski to planing speed in seconds.

The Suspension gives superb ride and handling on land and retracts when on the water. The complete transition takes four seconds, at the push of a button.
title: Gibbs Sports - Quadski High Speed Amphibious (HSA) Personal Watercraft [720p]

This is a program that retrieves images from a live video feed or from a video file stored in a drive and performs in real-time a color transformation to show how the video would be seen by one of the three kinds of dichromat color blind people. In this video, it's shown the transformation for people with deuteranopia.

The color transformation is based on the following paper: F. Viénot, H. Brettel, and J. Mollon. Digital video colourmaps for checking the legibility of displays by dichromats. Color Research and Application, 24:243-- 252, 1999.

More information at http://carlos.hernandez.im

description:
Die Fiegenstaller Kirche wurde mit der Weihe von Bischof Gundekar II urkundlich erstmals 1070 erwähnt. Vermutlich ist der Kirchturm schon viel älter. Mit der Friedhofsmauer diente sie lange dem Schutz vor Feinden. 

Im Jahre 1194 weihte Bischof Otto die Kirche zum zweiten Mal. Die dritte Konsekration erfolgte vermutlich 1402. 1598 wurde die  Kirche durch Bischof Johann Conrad von Gemmingen renoviert und ausstaffiert. Sein Wappen ist heute noch an der Ostseite des Turmes zu sehen. 

Von 1634-1664 war die Kirche in Folge des 30-jährigen Krieges verwüstet, leer und ohne Priester. Erst 50 Jahre nach Ende dieses unseligen Krieges regte sich in der Kirche wieder Leben. 1705 wurde mit der Reparatur der Turmhelms begonnen. 

1730 stiftete Walburga Hueber den Josefa-Altar. Der uralte Marienaltar wurde 1733 von 3 Guttätern neu gestiftet. 1736 folgte die Sanierung des Kirchenschiffs mit einem neuen Dachstuhl, einer Stuckdecke und einer Kanzel von Franz Horneis. 

Den Hochaltar fertigten Schreiner Winter und Maler Weber um 1800. Im vergangenen Jahrhundert gab es zwei große Renovierungen. 1936 wurden Innenraum und Altäre vom Kirchenmaler Johann Böckl renoviert. 

Die letzte große Erneuerung erfolgte 1990 unter Kirchenpfleger Heinrich Höppler.

description:
http://fertilitypartnership.com/infertility-glossary.html


The Beta hCG test this is a test to check for pregnancy. You can test it at home with a kit that you can get from a pharmacy where you dip your morning urine to see if you're pregnant. There is also a blood test. With this blood test we can check positive or negative or actually get an absolute quantity--a number that helps us understand how pregnant you are and how your pregnancy is progressing. 

Now Beta hCG was not developed or created to just let human beings know that they're pregnant. It has a purpose in the human body as a hormone that is secreted by the embryo after it implants into the wall. Its job is to send a message to the ovary to continue to secrete progesterone. 

When you go through an assisted reproductive procedure, we often trigger ovulation by giving you Beta hCG. It helps trigger ovulation, so you don't want to test too early because sometimes what you're measuring is the Beta hCH that you got from us, from the doctors, so you have to wait a certain amount of time to be sure that the Beta hCG that you're measuring is really coming from your embryo implanted into your uterus. 

At the Fertility Partnership we give instruction to our patients about when and how to test themselves.
title: Beta hCG Test Defined

description:
The key event in the development of feline infectious peritonitis (FIP) is the infection of the monocyte (a white blood cell) by feline coronavirus (FCoV).  From the moment of infection of the monocyte, the cat's fate hangs on whether or not that monocyte can contain the virus and eventually defeat it, or whether the virus wins, and begins replicating within the monocyte.  In this animation, we depict the latter.  We show how the virus hijacks the immune system, leading to an inflammatory sequence of events which results in a pyogranuloma forming around a blood vessel.  In the film we show the development of acute FIP, where there is a lot of virus, many blood vessels affected, and the resulting leakage from damaged blood vessels causes the clinical signs of effusive FIP -- ascites, thoracic effusion, pericardial effusion.  

In non-effusive FIP the course is more chronic: fewer blood vessels are affected, the cat's immune system tries harder to contain the infection, leading to larger pyogranulomata and the clinical signs of chronic inflammation and relating to the organ(s) containing the pyogranulomas.  

The catvirus.com website and You Tube channel are mainly aimed at postgraduate  veterinarians and undergraduate veterinary students, to supply information which is difficult to source elsewhere and to enable free online continuing professional development.  Non-veterinarians can find resources suitable for all cat lovers.at my website, www.catvirus.com.


Dr Diane D. Addie is a veterinary virologist with two dreams: to eradicate feline infectious peritonitis (FIP) from the face of the earth, and to find a cure for feline chronic gingivostomatitis.  You can read more about her work and these cat diseases on her website -- www.catvirus.com.  

Dr François Bagaini is a veterinary surgeon with a considerable talent for animation.  His veterinary cytology and haematology website is www.vetocyte.fr.    If you wish to contact him to commission an animation, his email address is bagaini.fr@vetocyte.fr
title: Pathogenesis of Feline Infectious Peritonitis (FIP) - the infection of the monocyte

description: The horse presented with a severe forelimb lameness. Infected material e.g. soil, grit had worked its way up between the hoof wall and the sole of the foot. This had resulted in a build up of pus within the hoof capsule and a consequent increase in pressure. This causes severe pain and therefore a reluctance for the horse to bear weight on the affected limb. The pus finds the plane of least resistance and bursts out just below the coronary band. This results in a dramatic decrease in the level of lameness. The coronary band was poulticed for 3 days to encourage drainage. The horse made a full recovery
title: Foot Abscess - pus bursting from hoof - erupting from the coronary band

description:
THEN: The formation of the UNA, the high threat of eco-terrorism, the mammoth rates of unemployment and subsequent escape into a world of virtual reality are things any student can read about in their 21st century textbooks and part of the normal background noise to Freya Kallas's life. Until that world starts to crumble.

NOW: It's 1985. Freya Kallas has just moved across the world and into a new life. On the outside, she fits in at her new high school, but Freya feels nothing but removed. Her mother blames it on the grief over her father's death, but how does that explain the headaches and why do her memories feel so foggy? When Freya lays eyes on Garren Lowe, she can't get him out of her head. She's sure that she knows him, despite his insistence that they've never met. As Freya follows her instincts and pushes towards hidden truths, the two of them unveil a strange and dangerous world where their days may be numbered. Unsure who to trust, Freya and Garren go on the run from powerful forces determined to tear them apart and keep them from discovering the truth about their shared pasts (and futures), her visions, and the time and place they really came from.
title: Yesterday official book trailer

الحديث


عن عائشة رضي الله عنها قالت دخل علي النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم وأنا أصلي وله حاجة فأبطأت عليه قال يا عائشة عليك بجمل الدعاء وجوامعه

وأسألك الجنة وما قرب إليها من قول أو عمل وأعوذ بك من النار وما قرب إليها من قول أو عمل 
وأسألك مما سألك به محمد وأعوذ بك مما تعوذ منه محمد 
وما قضيت لي من قضاء فاجعل عاقبته رشدا "



وفي روايه



" اللهم إني أسألك من الخير كله عاجله وآجله ما علمت منه وما لم أعلم وأعوذ بك من الشر كله عاجله وآجله ما علمت منه وما لم أعلم 
اللهم إني أسألك من خير ما سألك عبدك ونبيك وأعوذ بك من شر ما عاذ به عبدك ونبيك 
اللهم إني أسألك الجنة وما قرب إليها من قول أو عمل وأعوذ بك من النار وما قرب إليها من قول أو عمل

Với tài hoạt náo của mình, Đình Toàn đã thu hút được thêm nhiều bé tự tin tham gia nhảy Flash Mob. description:
This trailer is a preview of the full-length operation available at http://www.vjortho.com/2007/12/radial-head-arthroplasty-with-a-modular-metal-spacer/
This presentation, featuring David C. Ring, MD, PhD, Graham J.W. King, MD, MSc, FRCSC and Ruby Grewal, MD, MSc, FRCSC, covers Contraindications,
    "Pearls" on Avoiding Complications,
    Preoperative Planning -- Patient Selection,
    Exposure -- Key Anatomical Landmarks,
    Sizing -- Options in Perfecting Fit and
    Post Operative Protocol.
Comminuted fractures of the radial head are challenging to treat with open reduction and internal fixation. Radial head arthroplasty is an alternative treatment with results that compare favorably with those reported after open ORIF of similar fractures. In this JBJS/VJO video supplement, doctors Grewal and King from Ontario, Canada, discuss important intraoperative points while demonstrating their surgical technique for implanting a modular radial head prosthesis. Dr. David Ring, of Boston, Massachusetts, provides additional commentary on the surgical technique. A key feature of the design includes a stem that allows for rotational motion at both the implant/bone interface and radiocapitellar articulation, potentially reducing capitellar wear. There are 150 different combinations of heads and stems that permit minimal bone removal while optimizing fit.
title: Elbow Surgery: Radial Head Arthroplasty with a Modular Metal Spacer

description:
The Scharrel community wind farm at Saterland's Ostermoor bog in Germany is built with a focus on big wind turbines in order to generate "green" electrical power. Franz Bracht Kranvermietung specializes in heavy lifts and was hired to erect Enercon E-101 wind turbines at the wind farm. Reaching a hub height of 149 meters, these turbines are the largest models of the E-101 series. For the erection of these giants, the crane service provider relied on the capabilities of the new Terex® Superlift 3800 lattice boom crawler crane, which was developed with  this type of application in mind.

The new Superlift 3800 crawler crane showed its power and efficiency right from the setup on site. Thanks to the crane's lateral outriggers, the Bracht team erected it with much less ballast than would be necessary for other cranes of the same class and without an assist crane, reducing transport costs. "This not only shortens the setup time, but also means that fewer transportation trucks are required, which saves us money," says crane operator Michael Hildebrand. Thanks to its design to make assembly easy, the crane was fully set up with an SLS + LF_4, 153 m main boom and + 12 m LF superlift configuration in a mere two days -- ready to erect the wind turbines.
title: Terex Superlift 3800 crawler crane from Franz Bracht erecting Enercon E-101 150m wind turbines.

Tekst:

Wbijam na bit z nowym kawałkiem dla poległych,
Dla wszystkich którzy na moto zamknęli swe powieki.
Choć nie mogą nic powiedzieć to patrzą na nas z góry,
Bo jedna sytuacja i ich wzrok zakryły chmury.
Ten wzrok ponury, on towarzyszy ciągle,
Póki pamięć nie zginie oni będą żyli wiecznie.
Nasłuchali się w życiu, rzuć to, bo to niebezpieczne,
Pasja zwyciężyła a śmierć zabrała ich znów za wcześnie.
Tyle słyszy się w TV zginął motocyklista,
A 3/4 ludzi mówi dawca, bo pewnie jechał trzysta.
Takie są realia, taki jest dzisiejszy świat,
Chociaż byś jechał ostrożnie to i tak oskarżą Ciebie brat.
Tyle mówi się o śmierci Maliny, Bociana, Tomka,
A wciąż giną niewinni, ten track jest jak pochodnia.
Która zapłonie teraz gdy Ty go odpalasz,
Wspomnienie o wszystkich którzy zostawili życia bagaż.

Teraz składam hołd, składam i oddaję cześć,
Dla tych wszystkich poległych co od życia dostali pięść.
Jeden niefart, jedno wymuszenie osobówki,
Dla Ciebie wgniecione drzwi a dla nas koniec wędrówki. x2

Patrz w lusterka, motocykle są wszędzie,
Znane hasło, niech od dziś mottem Twoim będzie.
Nie wiesz jakie to uczucie składać się na zakręcie,
Wciąż gnać przed siebie i nie myśleć o tym co będzie.
A będzie dobrze brat i niczym się nie przejmuj,
Nawet jak nie masz sprzętu, bo liczy się pasja a nie fejm Twój.
Choć przyjęło się tak, że docenią Cie po śmierci,
Zamiast docenić za życia, tak jest ziomek wierz mi.
Najbardziej pamiętamy o tej Trójce wymienionej,
A co z resztą? Są równie ważni, człowiek!
Chociaż nie wybili się i nie było o nich słychać,
Zastanówmy się przez chwile, to dla nich ta muzyka.
Uszanuj to koleś i pomyśl choć przez chwilę,
Czy warto tak wcześnie kupić do nieba bilet.
Odbierz to jak przestrogę, przed tym co Cię czeka,

actually is not some emotional energy,

between their souls and the outside world.

let them believe in themselves
Let them be helpless like children,
because weakness is a great thing
and strength is nothing.

When a man is born,
he's weak and flexible,
when he dies, he is hard and insensitive.
When a tree is growing,
it's tender and pliant,
but when it dry and hard, it dies.

Hardness and strength are death's companions,
pliancy and weakness are expressions of the freshness of being.

description: This is an updated video on one method I use when candling lovebird eggs to check if they are fertile. I am candling using a small flashlight (Maglite is good). When using just a flashlight I find smaller ones are better as the larger ones will blur and not give you a good inside view of the egg. Next I "cradle" the egg gently between my thumb and index finger, making a ring so the egg is secure. Then I hold the flashlight under the egg and you get a pretty good view of the inside. I posted video of another method of candling using a homemade "candling box". This method can be a little tricky and must be done with care especially if doing it by yourself. What I like about using a candling box is you get a sharper all-over glow through the entire egg and you can see more detail, movement etc.  I also posted candling videos showing one week prior to this to show the growth progression.
title: 5-15-12 - Candling a fertile lovebird egg with easy flashlight method - this is baby Sweet Pea

Cassia javanica has almost no fragrance, has spreading branches to give shade, and is used as a [leguminous, nitrogenous!] very popular shade tree in tea gardens in India's north-east, and has pink clustered blossoming flowers.

Cassia javanica, also known as Java Cassia, Pink Shower, Apple Blossom Tree and Rainbow Shower Tree (Thai: ชัยพฤกษ์), is a species of tree in the Fabaceae family. Its origin is in Southeast Asia, but it has been extensively grown in tropical areas worldwide as a garden tree owing to its beautiful crimson and pink flower bunches.

It flowers from April to September; its flower is the provincial flower of Chainat Province, Thailand.

Bulgur Wheat and Paneer Pulao, nourshing and filling recipe!
Recipe link : http://www.tarladalal.com/Bulgur-Wheat-and-Paneer-Pulao-%28-Baby-and-Toddler-Recipe%29-3083r

Subscribe : http://goo.gl/omhUio

Tarla Dalal App: http://www.tarladalal.com/free-recipe-app.aspx
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/pages/TarlaDalal/207464147348
YouTube Channel: http://www.youtube.com/user/TarlaDalalsKitchen/featured
Pinterest: http://www.pinterest.com/tarladalal/
Google Plus:  https://plus.google.com/107883620848727803776
Twitter: https://twitter.com/Tarla_Dalal
Tarla Dalal Blogspot: http://tarladalal.blogspot.in/

Bulgur Wheat and Paneer Pulao

Pulao is usually associated with rice. Here, i have tried to make a different kind of pulao using bulgur wheat which has a very good fibre content. Addition of vegetables and paneer makes it all the more nourishing by adding protein and calcium as well as making it appealing for your infant. Serve it with fresh curds to make a complete meal.

Preparation Time: 5 minutes
Cooking Time: 15 minutes
Makes 1 cup

Ingredients
2 tbsp broken wheat (dalia) refer handy tip
1/4 cup paneer (cottagte cheese) cubes
1/2 tsp ghee
1/2 tsp cumin seeds (jeera)
1/2 cup finely chopped carrots
salt to taste

For The Garnish
1 tsp finely chopped coriander (dhania)

Method
1. Heat the ghee in a pressure cooker and add the cumin seeds.
2. When the cumin seeds crackle, add the broken wheat and sauté on a medium flame for 1 to 2 minutes.
3 .Add the carrots, paneer, salt and ¾ cup of water, mix well and pressure cook for 2 to 3 whistles.
4. Allow the steam to escape before opening the lid.
5. Garnish with coriander and serve lukewarm.

Handy tip:
Broken wheat is also known as bulgur wheat.
title: Bulgur Wheat and Paneer Pulao (Baby food -- 10 months and above) by Tarla Dalal

description:
O ''desvio de septo'' está entre as causas mais comuns de obstrução nasal persistente no adulto.
"Septo nasal", é uma estrutura ''laminar'' que, basicamente, 'divide' o nariz em duas narinas.
Frequentemente apresenta tortuosidades na sua conformação, que, podem gerar transtorno na dinâmica de fluxo do ar inspirado pelo nariz.
Pode ser uma causa isolada do distúrbio de fluxo aéreo nasal (nariz entupido), porém, em geral, se apresenta em conjunto com outras alterações anatômicas da cavidade nasal - em especial alteração no tamanho dos ''cornetos'' (ou turbinas, ou conchas nasais).
''Cornetos'' são estruturas ósteo-mucosas que se projetam da parede lateral da cavidade nasal, afim de aumentar a área de contato do ar inspirado com a ''mucosa nasal''.
Desta forma a eficiência das principais funções do nariz - aquecer, umidificar e 'filtrar' o ar inspirado que se dirige aos pulmões - se implementa.
No vídeo vemos a imagem de uma endoscopia nasal (exame solicitado sob o nome de Nasofibroscopia, ou Nasofibrolaringoscopia, videonasolaringoscopia, somente NASO, entre outros que são o mesmo exame...).
Dois componentes obstrutivos ao fluxo são apontados:
- A presença do desvio septal, em forma de 'esporão' na narina esquerda, que a obstrui quase totalmente.
Isso transfere a demanda de ar inspirado para a narina contra-lateral, - direita -.
- Insuficiência Valvular ou de Válvula Nasal:
Com o aumento da velocidade do ar que passa pela narina pérvia, se apresenta o chamado efeito de Bernoulli (força mecânica que se origina através da diminuição da pressão que o ar exerce sob superfície sólida, onde quanto mais velocidade, menos pressão, maior força de empuxo - é a base do funcionamento da asa do avião para levanta-lo do chão...).
Na região do vestíbulo nasal, provoca colapso da 'asa' do nariz (válvula nasal), acarretando à narina pérvia, neste caso, a obstrução completa do fluxo inspirado, devido ao colapso total da asa do nariz. 
Somente cirurgia corrige o septo tortuoso. 
Os cornetos são bem visualizados como estruturas ósteo mucosas que se projetam das paredes laterais - neste vídeo na narina direita, em especial - 
Por serem, os cornetos, quase na totalidade das vezes, fatores contribuintes ao nariz entupido, estes podem ser abordados cirurgicamente durante o mesmo tempo cirúrgico da septoplastia.
Procedimento denominado turbinoplastia ou turbinectomia. 
Este procedimento, hoje, se assume ser realizado preferivelmente por via endoscópica, assim  como demais procedimentos cirúrgicos intranasais como sinusotomias de cavidades paranasais (seios da face), exérese de tumores, pólipos, e acesso a glândula hipófise (até pouco tempo somente abordada via craniotomia externa) graças ao aprimoramento de tecnicas cirúrgicas via endoscópica endonasais pelo otorrinolaringologista bem aperfeiçoado, permitindo o acesso a base anterior do crânio e outras abordagens neurocirúrgicas que alguns anos requeriam abordagem via craniotomia (abertura do crânio) ou nem eram indicado cirurgia. 
Hoje, até mesmo a septoplastia também, vem sendo 'complementada' por cirurgia com visualização endoscópica, permitindo melhor visualização das estruturas a serem abordadas pelo cirurgião durante o ato cirúrgico.

Dr. Reinaldo Cóser Neto
title: Insuficiência valvular nasal - ''Naso, Nasofibro, Nasofibrolaringoscopia'' (endoscopia nasal).

description:
Watch more How to Do Coin Magic Tricks videos: http://www.howcast.com/videos/499450-How-to-Get-Started-Doing-Coin-Tricks-Coin-Tricks

Learn how to do the coin bend magic trick from celebrity magician Matt Wayne in this Howcast video.


Here's a great trick that you can do with a borrowed quarter.  All you have to do is borrow a quarter from someone, put it in your hand, and you're going to show them that you have superhuman strength by rubbing on that coin.  Just rub, rub, rub, rub, and push down on the coin, and then, hopefully, you're able to cause that coin to bend.  

Here's the explanation behind the coin bend magic trick.  All you need to do is borrow a coin from a friend and, before you borrow the coin from a friend, you have to make a bent coin up yourself.  Here's a very impromptu way of doing this.  Grab a hammer, take a coin, preferably a quarter. Go outside and, the pavement cracks in between the cement, stick the coin in one of those cracks. Take the hammer and hammer down on top of the coin. That coin, as you hammer it, will start to bend in half. It's a very impromptu way of bending a coin. Now if you have access to a vice, you're more than welcome to do it that way. Just turn it in the vice.  Make sure it's nice and tight and then hammer it that way.  But not everyone has a vice or a work shed, so you can go outside and make it by using the pavement.

Now that you have your bent quarter, you're ready to start the trick. Place the bent quarter on your middle finger and it will be nice and clipped because of the bend. Show the quarter to your audience. Come in. As you come in front of the coin, you're going to drop the quarter, but replace it with the bent coin. Like that. And you say that you're just going to start lightly start brushing the coin with your middle finger, like that.  As you do, you can make some sounds as if you're pushing on the coin, a grunt or whatever you'd like.  

When you're done rubbing, just remove your finger and show that the coin has bent.  As a bonus, if you'd like to show your friends that you have some psychic powers, you can then give the illusion that the coin is bending by holding it between your thumb and forefinger. If you push the coin up, it will naturally bow outward. And it's a perfect illusion, if done right.  And I highly recommend practicing it in front of a mirror.  As you say the word, "bend, bend, bend, bend," you push that coin up into view and it will give the illusion the coin is bending even further.  I hope you have fun with the coin bend magic trick.
title: How to Do the Coin Bend Trick | Coin Tricks

description: Michigan was one of the first starts to stop the sales of alcohol, ostensibly to protect families. Soon Detroit had many School Kids who sold Whiskey & Moonshine to adults in the Roaring 20's. Bootlegging operations and smuggling networks had formed within hours of Michigan's prohibition going into effect on May 1, 1917. With the Purple Gang and other syndicates violently profiting off liquor distribution, Michigan wised up and was the first state to ratify the 21st amendment, which repealed the 18th, and Prohibition officially ended on December 5, 1933.
title: Prohibition In Early 20th Century Detroit

description: Stewart Island Wood Pigeions feeding on the ground... New Zealand pigeons are commonly called wood pigeons but are not the same as the Wood Pigeon (Columba palumbus), which is a member of a different genus. The New Zealand Pigeon belongs to the family Columbidae, and the subfamily Treroninae, which is found throughout Southeast Asia, Malaya, Africa and New Zealand. The members of this subfamily feed largely on fruits, mainly drupes. New Zealand Pigeons are members of the pigeon genus Hemiphaga (Bonaparte, 1854), which is endemic to the New Zealand archipelago and Norfolk Island. However recently a Hemiphaga bone was found on Raoul Island. The Chatham Pigeon or Chatham Island Pigeon (Hemiphaga chathamensis) is traditionally considered a subspecies of the Kererū, but is here treated as a separate species.  The Kererū is protected under the Wildlife Act and there have been prosecutions for shooting it.
title: Wood Pigeon - Kererū NZ

„Heinrich Schütz. Die Gesamteinspielung": Unter Leitung von Hans-Christoph Rademann wird in den kommenden Jahren eine Einspielung aller Werke Heinrich Schütz' bei Carus erscheinen. Gemeinsam mit dem Dresdner Kammerchor, dem Dresdner Barockorchester und vielen namhaften Solisten werden die Werke historisch informiert in neuer Interpretation vorgelegt. Mit den "Psalmen Davids" erscheint im Oktober 2013 einer der Höhepunkte der Gesamteinspielung.
Eine Koproduktion mit MDR figaro.

"Heinrich Schütz -- The complete recording": In the coming years a recording of the complete works of Heinrich Schütz under the direction of Hans-Christoph Rademann will be released on the Carus label. Together with the Dresdner Kammerchor, the Dresdner Barockorchester and many renowned soloists these works, true to historical performance practice, will be presented. The "Psalmen Davids" (October 2013) mark one of the high points in the complete recording.
A coproduction with MDR figaro.
title: Heinrich Schütz: Psalmen Davids / Dresdner Kammerchor / Hans-Christoph Rademann

Mike Shiver finds himself once again stepping onto the illuminating stage of Enhanced with a debut original for the label in the form of an emotive new vocal single - 'The Shade'. Having teamed up with two talented singer/songwriters, Theresia Svensson & Johnny Norberg, the latter who has become a regular feature of late on Enhanced, Shiver manages to produce a captivating record that demonstrates his wonderful abilities with two brilliant mixes.

The Progressive Mix is a flurry of melodies and analogue styled synths whilst still capturing all the emotion in Svensson & Norberg's vocal mantra in a wonderfully classy progressive style.

On the flip side of this double edged release is the Club Mix. An altogether very different affair, this big room alternative is as technical as it is energetic. Staccato synths and EDM inspired FX make this track an ideal peak time trump card.

Not one, but two sterling mixes to choose from. Whether by the pool or in the club, 'The Shade' has it covered. A stunning outing from Mike Shiver feat. Theresia Svensson & Johnny Norberg! Huge early support from Tritonal and Armin van Buuren on ASOT!

description: 2009 წ. თბილისი. სინაგოგა" ბეით-რახელ". -  პირველი მარცხნივ თეთრ კოსტუმში დგას ჩემი თანაკლასელი - ამჟამად ამერიკელი მილიარდერი თამირ საფირი - თეიმურაზ სეფიაშვილი. Открытие в Тбилиси 15 09 2009 г. восстановленной Синагоги и названной " Бейт- Рахель "в память о матери главы Евроазиатского еврейского конгресса ( ЕАЕК ) главного спонсора Александра Машкевича. Спонсоры; Давид Якобашвили ,Тамир Сапир и другие. Первым слева в светлом костюме и в очках стоит улыбаясь один из основных спонсоров  ремонтно - реставрационных  работ,Теймураз Сепиашвили,он же американский миллиардер Tамир Сапир. В прошлом простой Тбилисский парень, из числа крутых ребят ( ძველი ბიჭი ). С ним мы дрались и дружили в 60 годах 20 века. Он был очень  интересной  личностью ! Мой одноклассник  по 45 средней школе  был как и я любителем бокса. Кто бы мог представить,что он станет МАРШАЛОМ БИЗНЕСА ! С 15 лет он участвовал  в школьных драках и бегал за красивыми девочками. Жил в центре старого Тбилиси,рядом с ( в 30 шагах  от и сейчас заброшенной,огромной,добротной из кирпича - с куполом со шпилем с которого по слухам пулей в 1992 году.сбили звезду Давида ) Ашкеназской Синагогой 19 века, в 2-х этажном, ветхом ,этого же века, коммунальном, жактовском с общим санузлом домике по ул. Ходашени № 14. Проходя возле его "домика ",встроенного за железными воротами в 4-х метровый вширь, сквозной, тесно заполненный в длину барачными жилыми пристройками дворик, вспоминаю наши годы и его весёлого,беспечного и не обременённого миллиардным состоянием. В последний раз,я его видел в  Москве  в 1984 году,когда я учился в Академии МВД СССР. Я с семьёй шёл в Цирк,расположенный на Цветном бульваре ,а он проезжал мимо. Остановившись,он рассказал мне,что организовал бизнес в Москве и предложил мне если, я хочу, достать видеотехнику.Мы расстались, и я его после этого не видел. В Тбилиси с ним встретиться не удалось. Наш Тбилисский друг  Темур ( Паписмедов ) Паписашвили рассказал мне,что находясь в США в 2008 году,позвонил к нему,но Т.Сапир его узнал только после того, как он назвал меня.Друг восторгался тем,как тот его хорошо принял !  Рад,что Темур Сепиашвили пригодился своему многострадальному народу,нашедшему в Грузии вторую родину. В настоящее время Евреи в Грузии живут гораздо лучше чем жили в эпоху СССР. Помню каким счастьем для них была возможность уехать из  СССР. Какие очереди на  оформление документов на выезд были в ОВИР-е МВД Грузии. Наглядно было понятно,что если бы в СССР жизнь была бы нормальной, то из страны бы, не был бы ,такой поток беженцев ! Сейчас же наоборот в Грузии и на благо Грузии достойно и добровольно проживает самодостаточная  ЕВРЕЙСКАЯ ДИАСПОРА ! - სერგო დავლიანიძე Серго Давлианидзе 20 01.2011 г.
title: The Marshal Of Business Мой одноклассник Темур Сепиашвили Tamir Sapir

description:
Perbedaan Jilbab, Hijab, dan Kerudung

Kerudung
pengertian kerudung sebenarnya sudah jelas. Kerudung umumnya dipakai oleh wanita muslim.Tetapi kerudung juga sering dipakai oleh perempuan non muslim. Kerudung sendiri tidak dianjurkan dalam Islam, karena desain kerudung cuma sebagai penutup kepala saja. Kerudung yang hanya sebagai penutup kepala, tidak sepanjang khimar yang mampu menutupi dada wanita sekaligus. 

Perempuan Yahudi Ortodoks yang sudah menikah, misalnya, diwajibkan untuk menutupi rambut mereka, seringkali menggunakan kerudung yang dikenal dengan nama tiche atau snood, sesuai dengan aturan kesopanan tzniot. Kerudung dulunya dipakai juga oleh perempuan Kristen yang telah menikah di Eropa pada abad pertengahan, bahkan dipakai juga oleh perempuan yang belum menikah.

Hampir sama dengan kerudung, ada istilah khimar. Sesuai yang tertera dalam surat An-Nur ayat 31 Khimar  adalah apa yang dapat menutupi kepala, leher dan dada tanpa menutupi muka. Khimar merupakan pakaian atas atau penutup kepala. Desain pakaian ini yaitu menutupi kepala, leher dan menjulur hingga menutupi dada wanita dari belakang maupun dari depan (termasuk menutupi tulang selangka). Khimar ini tidak diikatkan ke leher seperti kerudung, karena jika hal tersebut dilakukan, maka akan memperjelas bentuk lekuk dada dari wanita. Jadi khimar harus menjulur lurus kebawah dari kepala ke seluruh dada tertutupi.
Hijab
Hijab menurut Al-Quran artinya penutup secara umum. Allah SWT. dalam surat Al Ahzabayat 58 memerintahkan kepada para sahabat Nabi SAW  waktu mereka meminta suatu barang pada istri Nabi SAW untuk memintanya dari balik hijab. Jadi, hijab brarti umum, bisa berupa tirai pembatas.
Sehingga memang terkadang kata hijab dimaksudkan untuk makna jilbab. Adapun makna lain dari hijab adalah sesuatu yang menutupi atau menghalangi dirinya. Hijab berasal dari kata hajaban yang artinya menutupi, dengan kata lain al-Hijab adalah benda yang menutupi sesuatu.
Jilbab
Sebagaimana disimpulkan oleh Al Qurthuby: "Jilbab adalah pakaian yang menutupi seluruh tubuh". Kecuali Wajah dan telapak tangan.

description: When Nick Jaffe confessed to filmmaker Jack Rath that he was 'raw recruit' to sailing and needed to learn how because he was planning a 26.000 km passage around the world it was a clear subject for a film. Filmed over four years, 'Between Home' documents the odyssey of this Australian whiz-kid programmer. Beginning shortly after Jaffe purchases a second hand-boat in England, the film captures Jaffe's modulation of moods from high frequency stress to debased hilarity. Jaffe lives 'hand to mouth' while sinking deeper into debt and so invites the world to experience his dream through a blog that will help fund his voyage. And it works. The generosity of people wanting him to succeed is overwhelming yet it creates a paradox of added pressure from the world he's trying to retreat from. Alone at sea Jaffe keeps a video log, and answers questions given to him before departure. His philosophy appears to be a combination of auto-didacticism and 'gung ho libertarism' as he sails without permits or insurance.  At certain points on Jaffe's voyage, Rath catches up to him in Berlin, England, the Canary Islands, the Caribbean, Long Island, on a road trip across the U.S. As Jaffe voyages through the Pacific he encounters love, loss, and the ferocity of nature with a tsunami. As the sailor reaches his home shore Australia, the filmmaker meets him and captures Jaffe's abrupt confrontation with meaning of the term 'closure' in an unanticipated way.
title: BETWEEN HOME a film by Jack Rath (Trailer)

description: From VOA Learning English, welcome to Health in Special English! There is more evidence suggesting that being bilingual is good for your brain. A new study found that older adults who have spoken two languages since childhood showed better mental skills than those who speak just one language. Earlier studies showed that the ability to speak 2 languages, or bilingualism, seemed to favor the development of these heightened skills. The study appeared in the Journal of Neuroscience. Brian Gold was the lead author of the study. He is a neuroscientist at the University of Kentucky College of Medicine. Dr. Gold and his team asked people to sort colors and shapes in a series of simple exercises. They used brain imaging to compare how well three groups of people switched among these exercises. The groups were bilingual seniors, monolingual seniors and younger adults. The imaging showed different patterns of activity in the frontal part of the brain, in an area used for processing those tasks.  Dr. Gold says the results suggest that bilingual subjects use their brain more efficiently. Dr. Gold notes that knowing a second language made no difference for the young adults. They did better at the exercises than both groups of older people. But he says the older bilingual adults appear to have built up a surplus from a lifetime of increased mental activity. He says his research confirms an earlier study on bilingualism among patients with Alzheimer's disease. That study showed that bilingual speakers suffered more brain damage, but were able to think at the same level as patients with less damage. Dr. Gold says he believes the new study confirms that bilingualism can protect brain performance. For VOA Learning English, I'm Carolyn Presutti.
title: For the Brain, the Benefits of Being Bilingual

Richard Dawkins is a British ethologist, evolutionary biologist and popular science author. He was formerly Professor for Public Understanding of Science at Oxford University. He was voted Britain's leading public intellectual by readers of Prospect magazine and was named one of Time Magazine's "100 Most Influential People" for 2007.

Dawkins came to prominence with his 1976 book "The Selfish Gene", which popularised the gene-centred view of evolution and introduced the term "meme". He is a prominent critic of creationism and intelligent design. In his 1986 book "The Blind Watchmaker", he argued against the watchmaker analogy, an argument for the existence of a supernatural creator based upon the complexity of living organisms. Instead, he described evolutionary processes as analogous to a blind watchmaker. He has since written several popular science books, and makes regular television and radio appearances, predominantly discussing these topics.

Richard Dawkins is an atheist, secular humanist, sceptic, scientific rationalist, and supporter of the Brights movement. In his 2006 book "The God Delusion", he contends that a supernatural creator almost certainly does not exist and that faith qualifies as a delusion − as a fixed false belief.

description: Humpback whales performing a unique coordinated feeding behavior, called bubble-netting. In this behavior, several whales swim in a circle with the white underside of their pectoral fins turned to the inside of the circle. This causes the herring to swim in ever tighter circles. Another whale blows a stream of bubbles from underneath, causing the herring to rise to the surface. Yet another whale emits a call and coordinates a simultaneous breach of the surface by all the whales with their mouths wide open. The whales take as many fish as possible into their mouths, straining out the water.
title: Humpbacks Bubble-netting

The Amazing Scotty Brothers on spoons: Peter Scott, Gordon Scott accompanined by Tim Wheeler

March, 2013: The song has been picked up and sampled by the wonderful Sandra Boyton on her new album "Frog Trouble". The spoons can be heard on "I've Got a Dog" featuring the one and only Dwight Yokam. What an honor! Check for it in stores in the fall.

October 8th, 2011: Wow! We've reached the 100,000+ mark! Thanks so much to all of those who are enjoying this video and have taken the time to leave a comment. We love you. Please share it with your friends or a special someone that needs some cheering up! Best wishes from The Amazing Scotty Brothers!
July 30th, 2010:

Wonderful news - I was asked by the production team at NBC's "Tonight Show" if they could use this clip in a sketch Jay Leno was doing at the beginning of Friday's show! How amazing was that - we made it on America's biggest and longest running TV show! Hopefully that wasn't the be-all-and-end-all of our 15-seconds of fame! Thanks for the comments and support!

May 5, 2010: ***Wow! 41,000+ views! Thanks everybody for the great comments. Just to let you know that Gordon (the gentleman camera right) sadly passed away last year. He was a hardy old soul with a good heart and a matching sense of humour (which is perhaps why he wore his trouser so high). He served in the Merchant Navy most of his working life and survived several ship sinking escapes caused by German torpedoes in WWII. We miss him, but a bit of him lives on in those who have had the pleasure to have met him.

Peter (in the middle) is Gordon's younger brother. He is Brightlingsea born and bred and spent his working life on top of people's rooftops mending their broken television aerials. Peter cunningly mixed his work with pleasure,  a keen photographer  - he now boasts one of the largest collection of rooftop scenes of the coastal town of Brightlingsea in the entire coastal town of Brightlingsea!

Both of these "Scotty Brothers" are some of the last great spoon players of a generation who had some spoons and each other to play with growing up. They have played spoons together since a very young age which shows in their tacit, yet perfect,  timing.

The chap playing guitar is me, Tim Wheeler.

Thanks for watching and reading! Please continue leaving your wonderful comments!
title: Playing Spoons - Amazing Scotty Brothers
